                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This is not an issue; if you examine the code of {{_doUpdate()}}, you'll see that this functionality already exists. For example:\n\n{noformat}\n        \/**\n         * Compare the data to the modified fields array to discover\n         * which columns have been changed.\n         *\/\n        $diffData = array_intersect_key($this->_data, $this->_modifiedFields);\n{noformat}\n\nPlease feel free to reopen if I have missed something. :)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=darby",
                        "name": "darby",
                        "displayName": "Darby Felton",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-04-21T12:33:16.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-04-21T12:33:16.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/21235",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexl",
                        "name": "alexl",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Lanin",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "array_intersect_key() does not evaluate the value at all. I just checks the keys.\nhttp:\/\/de.php.net\/manual\/en\/function.array-intersect-key.php\n\nand {code}$this->_modifiedFields[$columnName] = true;{code} is just \"true\" anyway\n\nso I think whats happening is that doUpdate updates all fields, even if value was \"changed\" but remains the same.\n\nmaybe you didn't understood my point. I was saying that when sql returns me a \"name=fritz\" and I do tableRow->name = \"fritz\" than I did *not* change the value - no need to include it into doUpdate()",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=alexl",
                        "name": "alexl",
                        "displayName": "Alexander Lanin",
                        "active": false
